title: Net Portfolio Holdings of LLCs funded through the Money Market Investor Funding Facility (DISCONTINUED)
notes:
On November 24, 2008, the Money Market Investor Funding Facility (MMIFF) was created to provide funding to a series of limited liability companies to purchase short-term U.S. dollar-denominated certificates of deposit, bank notes, and outstanding asset-backed commercial paper.
For more information, visit http://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/mmiff.htm.
